    {
      "id": "p004",
      "index": 4,
      "source": "In the case of the MI325X, it appears that not all performance enhancements that were present in the downstream ROCm fork image (used during the October 5th, 2025 run) have made it into the official vLLM ROCm image. Unfortunately, the MI355X literally still uses a fork of the vLLM 0.10.1 build rocm/7.0:rocm7.0_ubuntu_22.04_vllm_0.10.1_instinct_20250927_rc1). We would love to have seen it updated it by now, but unfortunately the current official image (0.15.1, at the time this article was written) is not yet optimized for the MI355X and runs into hard errors. We had also run into hard errors crashes on Mi355 for vLLM 0.14. Word on the street is that vLLM 0.16.0 will finally deliver all the changes needed for better MI355X performance.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [
        {
          "type": "code",
          "text": "rocm/7.0:rocm7.0_ubuntu_22.04_vllm_0.10.1_instinct_20250927_rc1",
          "start": 295,
          "end": 358,
          "href": null,
          "title": null,
          "span_id": "CODE_1"
        }
      ],
      "parent_block_id": "b0079",
      "parent_block_index": 79,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "In the case of the MI325X, it appears that not all performance enhancements that were present in the downstream ROCm fork image (used during the October 5th, 2025 run) have made it into the official vLLM ROCm image. Unfortunately, the MI355X literally still uses a fork of the vLLM 0.10.1 build `rocm/7.0:rocm7.0_ubuntu_22.04_vllm_0.10.1_instinct_20250927_rc1`). We would love to have seen it updated it by now, but unfortunately the current official image (0.15.1, at the time this article was written) is not yet optimized for the MI355X and runs into hard errors. We had also run into hard errors crashes on Mi355 for vLLM 0.14. Word on the street is that vLLM 0.16.0 will finally deliver all the changes needed for better MI355X performance.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "In the case of the MI325X, it appears that not all performance enhancements that were present in the downstream ROCm fork image (used during the October 5th, 2025 run) have made it into the official vLLM ROCm image. Unfortunately, the MI355X literally still uses a fork of the vLLM 0.10.1 build rocm/7.0:rocm7.0_ubuntu_22.04_vllm_0.10.1_instinct_20250927_rc1). We would love to have seen it updated it by now, but unfortunately the current official image (0.15.1, at the time this article was written) is not yet optimized for the MI355X and runs into hard errors. We had also run into hard errors crashes on Mi355 for vLLM 0.14. Word on the street is that vLLM 0.16.0 will finally deliver all the changes needed for better MI355X performance.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [
        {
          "type": "code",
          "text": "rocm/7.0:rocm7.0_ubuntu_22.04_vllm_0.10.1_instinct_20250927_rc1",
          "start": 295,
          "end": 358,
          "href": null,
