    {
      "id": "p007",
      "index": 7,
      "source": "Turning back to Nvidia’s systems, both Hopper and Blackwell saw a steady performance increase between vLLM 0.11.2 and 0.13.0. Soon, we will update recipes for Nvidia GPUs to use the latest vLLM version and we expect even greater performance gains after making the switch. We also observed a performance bump in the latest 1.2.0 version of TRT-LLM.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0082",
      "parent_block_index": 82,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "Turning back to Nvidia’s systems, both Hopper and Blackwell saw a steady performance increase between vLLM 0.11.2 and 0.13.0. Soon, we will update recipes for Nvidia GPUs to use the latest vLLM version and we expect even greater performance gains after making the switch. We also observed a performance bump in the latest 1.2.0 version of TRT-LLM.",
